## Biography (Realbubblegum)

Hello I am Ruslana. I'm 18 years old and I'm from Ukraine. I live in Kiev and go to the Circus University. Since I was a little child I love the art of contorsion. I enjoy bending my body extremely. Already at the age of 6 years I had my first big show as a snake woman. My back is extremely soft and flexible. Normally I only need 5 minutes to warm me up. After that I am able to fold my back completely. I do not need a warm-up to do a balancing act. I can always do a balancing act and in any form. You can view and book my gala and event shows here. ## Biography

Maria Sarach is a contortionist from Moscow, Russia. She is the daughter of Alexei Sarach and Tatyana Basargina, also circus artists<sup>[1](https://web.archive.org/web/20100211012043/http://ffg2000.narod.ru/names/index.htm)</sup>.

## Biography (maria-sarach.com)

Maria Sarach was born in 1989. She comes from a famous Russian circus family and she was always dreaming to became the artist like her parents. The mother Tatyana started to stretch the daughter from 3-4 years old. At 14 Maria took part in the perch-pole balancing act of her father Alexei Sarach the People's artist of Russia, the creator of the unit record tricks at the big hight, but Maria has opted for a genre of solo plastic equilibre. Already at the beginning of the carrier she became an owner of the Silver Crown at the "Princess of Russian Circus" Festival in Saratov. Maria continued to work with the famous directors such as Olga and Yan Poldy, Giulio Scatola, Elena Serafimovich, Olga Pikhienko and created few acts which performed on the best stages of the circus world including Las Vegas and Cirque Du Soleil.

## Biography (Flexshow)

Masha was born in a family of famous circus artists. Aleksej Sarach, Masha's father, a world-renowned national artist of the Russian Federation, is in charge of the record breaking team of acrobats. Masha made her first appearance in 2003 during Alekseij's benefit performance. Ever since, Masha moves in the same direction as her parents, but in her own, personal way. As of right now, Masha holds the official title of the "Princess of the Russian Circus". In the mean time, Masha is a part-time undergraduate student at Moscow Linguistic University. She is majoring in the German Language studies and plans on pursuing carrier in translation services.
zbgsIVGd.name: Maria Sarach
